text: Two ships of the Royal Navy have borne the name HMS Jalouse after the French word meaning jealous, suspicious, or wary: * HMS Jalouse was the 18-gun French Navy brig-corvette Jalouse launched in 1794 at Honfleur. The Royal Navy captured her in May 1797; she was broken up in 1807. * was a launched in 1809 and sold in 1819. Category:Royal Navy ship names
title: HMS Jalouse
